  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Urgent stabilization and rehabilitation works of the Fort at English Komenda, Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Fort at British Komenda is a component of the serial World Heritage property Forts and Castles, Volta, Greater Accra, Central and Western Regions inscribed on UNESCO&apos;s World Heritage List in 1979. In July 2021, while GMMB officials were undertaking preparatory works to reconstruct a damaged plinth at a section of the Fort at British Komenda, the external wall at the section under repair, crumbled. There is urgent need to stabilize and rehabilitate the collapsed wall and to implement other key repair/consolidation works on sections of the Fort.</narrative>
  </description>
